Problem Statment 2

      As the coronavirus pandemic continues to spread, The U.S. has seen More then 200,000  deaths’ and more then 8,000.000 Cases’ so far this year, according to government data, and the new coronavirus accounts for much but not all  of the increase.  It’s likely the virus was a factor in many other deaths too. Public health experts say that if Americans adopted even the simplest measures discussed for months, it could make a big difference. That includes universal mask-wearing, physical distancing, avoiding crowds and hand-washing
